{"role":"assistant","message":{"content":[{"type":"text","text":"The company workspace now surfaces the original job posting right after **Download PDF**, with a clear apply step.\n\n**Changes:**\n\n1. **`company.html`** — Moved the apply action to after Download PDF as **Apply on company site**, and added a hint line with the full original URL below the action buttons.\n\n2. **`company.js`** — Wires both the button and the URL from `position.url`. When a PDF exists, the hint reads: *\"After downloading your PDF, apply at the original posting:\"* followed by the clickable URL.\n\n3. **`styles.css`** — Styling for the hint and URL link (muted text, accent-colored link, word-break for long URLs).\n\n**Flow on the company page:**\n1. Download PDF  \n2. Click **Apply on company site** (or the URL in the hint below)  \n3. Apply on the company’s ATS\n\nThe URL comes from the catalog `matching_jobs` entry, same as before — it’s just placed for the post-download workflow.\n\n[REDACTED]"}]}}
